  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.3537" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <opener>Dear Professor Schuchardt, </opener>
        <p>I might say much to you about the perfidy of <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1054">Arzac</persName> who has never returned some of my longer manuscripts, nor published some which he promised to publish, and that of the President of the <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.subjects#S.4686">Society Ramond</ref> who two years ago promised to publish my edition of the Pastoral of S<hi
            rendition="#sup">t</hi>. Hélène &amp; any other pastoral I might offer, or any other of my Bascological works, but who, though he quite recently repeated his promise &amp; has published it in the Bulletin of last year with the notice that the government had granted the Society 500 francs for the purpose, returned the manuscript on my arrival here without any explanation. He has not called on me, though I have been 5 times to his house without finding him at home, nor answered my notes asking for an explanation. So Bascology is a martyrdom. But there is an Irish proverb which says that one must not complain till we know whether those who hear us will sympathize, and I fear you are no friend of mine. M<hi
            rendition="#sup">r</hi>. <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1466">Van Eys</persName> seems to be pleased to have made your acquaintance. I gather from M<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi>
          <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2047">Linschmann</persName>s last letter that Euskara 16 may be the last. Can you do nothing to keep an old friend alive? He does not grant me space to make some important additions and corrections to my already published writings in former numbers. <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1294">De Charencey</persName>s society is kindly having my Concordance to the Epistles to S<hi
            rendition="#sup">t</hi>. Timothy printed. I have corrected two proofs already. I have not yet had the proof of my collection of Basque inscriptions which father <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1491">F. Fita</persName> talked of sending me. D<hi rendition="#sup">r</hi>
          <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1805">E. Hübner</persName> accepted the dedication in Basque though he only knows me by letter, and modestly disclaims knowing Basque. I am not satisfied with the explanation of tarde piache given by M<hi rendition="#sup">me</hi>
          <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2194">C. de Vasconcellos</persName>. She did not answer about <foreign xml:lang="ar">
            <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">maidah</hi>
          </foreign> in Arabic translating Basque <foreign xml:lang="eu">
            <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">
mahaina</hi>
          </foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="eu">
            <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">maya</hi>
          </foreign>. Here they say toi &amp; choi = petit. is it Spanish <foreign
            xml:lang="es">chico</foreign>? In a valley near here they say chec I hear. A messmate here thinks it is from <hi
            rend="unknown" rendition="#none">
toza</hi>. I do not agree. I am still unable to verify your<note n="1"
            place="foot"
            type="editorial">Fortsetzung am rechten Rand.</note> accusation about acheter. If you are right I shall make an<note
            n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">Fortsetzung kopfüber am oberen Rand.</note> amende honorable.</p>
        <closer>
          <signed>
            <persName ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.1402">E. S. Dodgson</persName>.</signed>
          <dateline>6 May, 1895. Hotel Vignes, Bagnères de Bigorre. H. P.</dateline>
        </closer>
        <postscript>
          <p>
            <note n="3" place="foot" type="editorial">Randnotiz auf der linken Seite.</note> The Curé of Luc is publishing a grammar of the Bigorre patois.</p>
        </postscript>
        <pb facs="#IMG.2" n="2"/>
      </div>
